*Costs are approximate and may vary by supplier and location. Assumes access to tools for fabrication.*

## Component Substitutions

**Acceptable Alternatives:**

- **Arduino:** Any compatible board with 20+ I/O pins (Mega, Due, etc.)
- **Multiplexers:** 74HC4067 (non-CD variant) works identically
- **Resistors:** 820Ω to 1.5kΩ range acceptable (adjust for LED specs)
- **LEDs:** Any small LEDs with appropriate voltage/current ratings

**Not Recommended:**

- Arduino Uno (insufficient pins even with multiplexers)
- Higher resistance values (>2kΩ) may produce dim LEDs
- Non-pre-wired LEDs (significantly increases assembly time)

## Inventory Checklist

Use this checklist when gathering components:

- [ ] Arduino Mega 2560
- [ ] 4× CD74HC4067 multiplexers
- [ ] 4× 1kΩ resistors
- [ ] 75× pre-wired LEDs (or more for spares)
- [ ] 4× prototyping boards
- [ ] 64× 3D printed tiles (32 light, 32 dark)
- [ ] 1× acrylic base
- [ ] 32× chess pieces (1 complete set)
- [ ] Hookup wire assortment
- [ ] Heat shrink tubing
- [ ] Solder
- [ ] Access to required tools

## Notes

- Order extra LEDs (recommend 80+) to account for potential failures
- Keep all receipts for project documentation
- Check component compatibility before purchasing
- Consider prototyping one quadrant before full assembly
